Subshells
---------

Process list
-------------

    (pwd ; ls)
    (sleep 5 ; pwd ; echo  '\n' ; ls)
    (sleep 2 ; echo 'ti cio')


Pipes
------

Co-processes
------------
    coproc (tar -xf xx.tar obj1 obj2; ls)



A shell instance can be started in multiple ways

-c string, Reads commands from string and process them
-i, Starts an interactive shell, allwoing input from the user
-l, Acts as if invokes as a login shell
-r, Starts a restricted shell, limiting the user to the default directory
-s, Reads commands from the standard intput
